    "There has been an increase in STEM educationrelated academic work in China in the last several years (Meng et al. 2022).",
    "These studies shed light on the changing educational landscape in the country by investigating various STEM-related subjects (Ma, 2021).",
    "Most of this research can be categorized into four key areas: conceptual frameworks, strategies for implementing STEM education, curriculum design, and empirical studies that apply theoretical concepts in practice.",
    "While these studies contribute valuable insights, they highlight a critical need to transition from abstract theories about STEM education to practical applications, particularly within teacher professional development (TPD) (Zhou and Li, 2021a, 2021b).",
    "This shift involves examining how STEM concepts are taught, how STEM teachers are prepared, and the development of effective teaching models (Ryu et al. 2019; Zhong et al. 2022)."
  ],
